<title>
Broccoli Salad
</title>
<details>
AUTHOR: i heart eating
PREP TIME: 20 minutes
TOTAL TIME: 20 minutes
COURSE: Salad
CUISINE: American
KEYWORD: broccoli
SERVINGS: 12
</details>
<ingredients><ingredient amount="">Salad</ingredient><ingredient amount="5.0 Cup">Broccoli</ingredient><ingredient amount="1.0 Cup">Carrot</ingredient><ingredient amount="1.0 Cup">Celery</ingredient><ingredient amount="0.5 Cup">Cheddar</ingredient></ingredients>
<instructions>
In a large bowl, stir together vegetables, cheese, bacon, 3/4 cup sunflower seeds, and cranberries.
Whisk mayonnaise, yogurt, sugar, vinegar, salt, and pepper together in a small bowl.
Add dressing to salad, and toss to combine.
Cover, and refrigerate until chilled.
Serve cold, and top with remaining 1/4 cup sunflower seeds just before serving.
</instructions>
<cuisine>American</cuisine></recipe>